'''Pre-primary education in [[Mauritius]]''' is the stage of education to be completed prior to the start of [[Primary education in Mauritius|primary school]], which is compulsory for all students of ages 3 to 5 in Mauritius. The pre-primary programme of study lasts for three years, termed as Year 1, Year 2, and Year 3. Upon completion of the pre-primary years of study, students may enter into primary school, which continues to the award of the [[Certificate of Primary Education]] for students who successfully complete primary school studies with passing marks on the final exams.

